{
  "stem": "1511.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On the way before we came, we stopped the train.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[SOBBING] We all went and picked up hair, and what do you call this?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Braids, hands, clothes, where the German couldn't-- they just-- and they were all open, and we had the Lubavitch.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we digged a big grave, and we covered them all with our hands, with things, and we [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] prayed [SOBBING] and said Kaddish and kept going.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was terrible experience.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then when we came to Austria, and the Bricha put us in this places where the Germans kept all the Jewish people from all over the world.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we slept in that barracks-- 10 families, five families.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We're just a little over in the middle.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we used to go every morning for food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We couldn't cook.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We didn't do anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My daughter was small.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "She couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She was like a finger.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She was already almost a year, a year, maybe old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I used to go to-- in Vienna-- in Austria, sell what the Americans used to give us-- a bit of chocolate and things like that to sell it in case to buy for her an egg or food.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And every morning, we would get up, and they'd give us milk, you know, and-- and my husband right away went to the-- like, they had a committee.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There is one woman.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She's here.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Her husband was the lagerfeuhrer, they called him, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Start coming clothes and things from America, and they start giving us clothes, and dressing us up and things like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it was very tragic in this concentration where we lived, because you find all kinds-- it was very scared.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
